{{short description|Fifteenth-century English poem}}
{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Knyghthode and Bataile''}}
'''''Knyghthode and Bataile''''' was a [[fifteenth-century]] verse paraphrase by [[John Neele]]<ref>Wakelin, D., 'The Occasion, Author, and Readers of Knyghthode and Bataile,' ''Medium Aevum'', 73 (Autumn, 2004)</ref> of [[Vegetius Renatus]]' treatise ''[[De Re Militari]]''. Influenced by the years of English occupation of France, and completed ''circa'' November 1459 to June 1460, it has been called 'one of the most brilliant military poems of the fifteenth century.'<ref>Nial, C., ''Sacralising Warfare in "Knyghthode and Bataile"'', Woodbridge 2012, p. 14</ref> It was published in a modern edition by the [[Early English Text Society]] in 1935, and most recently by [[Boydell and Brewer]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boydellandbrewer.com/store/viewItem.asp?idProduct=9720|title=Knyghthode and Bataile (Edited by R. DyboskiEdited by Z.M. Arend) 9780859916943 - Boydell & Brewer|author=This web site is designed and hosted Biznetix - Your Business Internet Experts|work=Boydell & Brewer}}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

