'''Nikolai Afanasyevich Kryuchkov''' ({{lang-ru|Николай Афанасьевич Крючков}}; 6 January 1911 &ndash; 13 April 1994) was a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] film actor. He appeared in 94 films between 1932 and 1993.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/obituary-nikolai-kryuchkov-1371355.html|location=London, UK|work=The Independent|first=Jeanne|last=Vronskaya|title=Obituary: Nikolai Kryuchkov|date=20 April 1994}}</ref>
==Biography== Nikolay Kryuchkov was born on December 24, 1910 (January 6, 1911) in Moscow, in a working family.
